Abstract: Robin Finn article says physical malformations and other ill effects of dog breeding should serve as warning to those eager to improve human species through genetic engineering; photo (M)
Snippet: Robin Finn article says physical malformations and other ill effects of dog breeding should serve as warning to those eager to improve human species through genetic engineering; photo (M)
LeadParagraph: FOR those who wonder where genetic engineering may take man in the future, it might be instructive to look at what man has already wrought on his supposed best friend. In the $2 billion canine industry, designer dogs rule.

Headline.Main: It Shouldn't Happen To a Dog
